This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Scheduling conference on November 23, 2022 at 02:00 pm.

2:46 PM Defendant Tommy R. Goebel in court.  Attorney Corinne Frutiger in court for State of Wisconsin. 

Defendant informs Court he has not retained counsel yet but is awaiting a call back from an attorney he has access to through his employment.
Court informs defendant of right to counsel.
Court determines that defendant's failure to retain an attorney by today's hearing is a waiver of counsel.
State does not have an issue with proceeding forward today with arraignment.
Court reads charging portion of complaint into the record.
Defendant enters plea of "not guilty" to Counts 1 and 2.
Set for scheduling 11/23/22 at 2:00 p.m. (15 min - in person)

4:18 PM 
Defendant Tommy R. Goebel in court.  Attorney Jenna L Gill in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Defendant once again is informed of his right to counsel and provided with the PD information.
Defendant is provided with the information.
Court reads information.

Court will continue arraignment one final time.
If defendant fails to retain counsel by his next hearing he waives his right to counsel.
Arraignment scheduled for October 26, 2022 at 02:45 pm.

2:30 PM 
Defendant Tommy R. Goebel in court.  Attorney Jenna L Gill in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Defendant is informed once again he has the right to retain counsel.
Defendant does NOT qualify for court appointment of counsel.
Court finds defendant has waived her right to counsel for preliminary hearing today due to lack of retaining counsel.

State calls Corporal Ryan Redfearn to the stand.
**Ryan Redfearn is affirmed.
Direct examination by the State.
No questions by the defendant.

Court finds probable cause and orders defendant be bound over for arraignment.

State files informs.
Defendant is provided with a copy.

Bond continues.
Arraignment scheduled for August 24, 2022 at 03:20 pm.
Preliminary hearing on July 20, 2022 at 02:30 pm.

11:49 AM Defendant Tommy R. Goebel appeared by video means. Prosecuting Atty Jenna Gill appeared for State of Wisconsin. Attorney Jenna L Gill in court for Plaintiff State of Wisconsin.  (Court reporter:  Paige Reardon recording remotely)

Court informs defendant of rights.
Court reads charging portion of complaint into the record.
Defendant acknowledges receipt of complaint.
Defendant informs Court that he is trying to get the money together to retain counsel.
Set for preliminary hearing 07/20/22 at 2:30 p.m.
Adjourned initial appearance on May 25, 2022 at 11:45 am.
